text: Spartanburg is a city in and the seat of Spartanburg County, South Carolina, United States. It is the 11th-largest city by population in the state. The city of Spartanburg has a population of 38,732 as of the 2020 census. The Spartanburg Metropolitan Statistical Area, including Spartanburg and Union counties, had a population of 355,241 as of the 2020 census. ==References== Category:Cities in South Carolina Category:County seats in South Carolina
title: Spartanburg, South Carolina
